Rule 16.6 Every switch statement shall have at least two switch-clauses
Category Required
Analysis Decidable, Single Translation Unit
Applies to C90, C99
Rationale
A switch statement with a single path is red undant and may be indicative of a programming er ror.
Example
switch ( x )
{
default: /* Non-compliant - switch is redundant */
x = 0;
break;
}
switch ( y )
{
case 1:
default: /* Non-compliant - switch is redundant */
y = 0;
break;
}
switch ( z )
{
case 1:
z = 2;
break;
default: /* Compliant */
z = 0;
break;
}
See also
Rule 16.1
